made sure mask changes show up when 'skipUnchangedFrames' is enabled

When a mask doesn't have a parent, a call to 'setRequiresRedraw' doesn't propagate up to the stage, and so 'skipUnchangedFrames' might lead to the change not becoming visible. This commit prevents that. Thanks to Josh Tynjala for the report!

Here's a sample that showcases the scenario.

    var quad1:Quad = new Quad(200, 200, 0x339933);
    quad1.x = 10;
    quad1.y = 10;
    this.addChild(quad1);

    var quad2:Quad = new Quad(200, 200, 0xff00ff);
    quad1.mask = quad2;

    Starling.juggler.tween(quad2, 5, {width: 0});

Add "requiresRedraw" to starling.text.TextField

Please add "requiresRedraw" to starling.text.TextField

final protected function requiresRedraw():void 
{
	mRequiresRedraw = true;
}

I need it in my class:

public class WordWrapTextField extends starling.text.TextField
{
	private var mWordWrap:Boolean;
 
	override protected function formatText(textField:flash.text.TextField, textFormat:TextFormat):void
	{
		super.formatText(textField, textFormat);
		textField.wordWrap = mWordWrap;
	}
	 
	public function get wordWrap ():Boolean { return mWordWrap }
	public function set wordWrap (value:Boolean):void
	{
		mWordWrap = value;
		super.requiresRedraw();
	}
}

Thanks.

fixed wrong BitmapData size in 'drawToBitmapData' when using HiDPI display (closes #618)

Starling now contains properties for both "backBufferWidth/Height" and "viewPortWidth/Height";
one returns the actual size in pixels, the other in points. This is necessary because Stage3D is inconsisent with its back buffer dimensions. Some methods (e.g. 'setScissorRectangle') use points, others (e.g. 'backBufferWidth/Height') use pixels.

forgot to clear queue after processing in last commit (refs #502)

Furthermore, aborting queue processing should now work in all cases again;
and you can make several "loadQueue" calls simultaneously now.

fixed bug introduced with previous AssetManager change

At the same time, this change allows to change the texture settings while filling up the queue.
In the following sample, the first bunch of textures will use mipmaps, the second bunch won't.

    assets.useMipMaps = true;
    assets.enqueue(appDir.resolvePath("textures/with-mipmaps"));
    assets.useMipMaps = false;
    assets.enqueue(appDir.resolvePath("textures/without-mipmaps"));
